Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. In a large skillet cook sausage, onion and garlic until browned, drain well. Stir in RED GOLD(R) or REDPACK(R) CRUSHED TOMATOES and mushrooms. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Hollow out bottom half of bread loaf. Spoon meat mixture into hollowed out bread. Arrange cheese over meat and top with red peppers. Replace top of loaf and wrap tightly with foil. Place on a baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes, or until heated through. Cut into 2 inches wide slices.